Comment: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:23.76,title,,0,0,0,,Mezase eikou no hoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.48,0:02:33.12,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:  The Tokyo Big6 is a championship between six colleges in the Tokyo area.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:34.91,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima hits his eighth homerun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:37.36,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:  Nagashima Shigeo was a famous baseball player. \N He played for the Yomiuri Giants during his professional career.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.03,0:02:37.36,star,,0,0,0,,This is his eighth homerun in the Big6!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.75,0:02:41.34,star,,0,0,0,,The hero of the championship, Rikkyou University's third baseman, Nagashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:44.15,star,,0,0,0,,Holding his victory in his hands, Nagashima looks ecstatic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.78,0:02:51.78,star,,0,0,0,,- Nagashima-san, what team did you choose? \N{\c&HFFFFFF&} -  Please tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.84,0:02:58.16,star,,0,0,0,,Kawakami-san, what do think of the up-and-coming Nagashima-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.84,0:02:58.16,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:  Kawakami Tetsuharu was a famous batter, known as the "God of Batting". He played for the Giants until 1958.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:01.09,star,,0,0,0,,- He's so dreamy! \N {\c&HFFFFFF&}- He really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.09,0:03:02.53,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima's a real looker, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:04.92,star,,0,0,0,,At the end of 1957...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.56,0:03:07.48,star,,0,0,0,,It was decided that the star \Nathlete of the Tokyo Big6...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:09.48,star,,0,0,0,,...Third Baseman, Nagishima...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.56,0:03:12.08,star,,0,0,0,,...would be admitted into the Giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:19.56,star,,0,0,0,,The new star of the Giants: \NThe Golden Rookie, Nagashima.
Comment: 0,0:03:19.56,0:03:21.56,star,,0,0,0,,\soshite shigyo saikou no mei sanruishi tanjou to otona mo kodomo mo otoko mo onna mo nagashima no uwasa. nagashima kouban  /
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:24.12,star,,0,0,0,,What followed the announcement was the \N greatest debut of any famed third baseman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:28.40,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima's name was on the lips of everyone, \N regardless of their age and gender.
Comment: 0,0:03:28.40,0:03:30.40,star,,0,0,0,,nagashima no hyouban ni wa fukatsu. nagashima no ninki wa yaga uwe ni noboriagate ita
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.54,0:03:31.13,star,,0,0,0,,His reputation kept growing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:34.77,star,,0,0,0,,...and his popularity climbed with each passing day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.15,0:03:37.62,star,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.48,0:03:41.01,star,,0,0,0,,There was one person who couldn't \Nbe bothered to listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:43.34,star,,0,0,0,,A lone young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:51.05,star,,0,0,0,,You're such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.05,0:03:53.37,star,,0,0,0,,There's no way Nagashima would do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.57,0:03:56.81,star,,0,0,0,,He'd pull the coolest home run \Nand get it on his first try!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:57.88,star,,0,0,0,,You got that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:04:00.10,star,,0,0,0,,He {\i1}is{\i0} the Golden Rookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:03.10,star,,0,0,0,,But y'know, his opponent is Kaneda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.44,0:04:04.78,star,,0,0,0,,He can't win that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:04.78,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:  Kaneda Masaichi was a famous Japanese pitcher who played for the Kokutestu Swallows. In Nagashima's debut match, Nagashima was struck out by Kaneda four times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:07.82,star,,0,0,0,,Stupid! No matter what you say, it's gonna be Nagashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.82,0:04:09.11,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima's gonna win!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:11.57,star,,0,0,0,,Hm, of course, but what can one say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:12.76,star,,0,0,0,,The truth of the matter is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.76,0:04:16.44,star,,0,0,0,,...not one person will know the outcome until\N it happens, is that not true for every match?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:16.45,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:  He's imitating a sports reporter. I tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.25,0:04:20.31,star,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:23.02,star,,0,0,0,,Stop talking about Nagashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.82,0:04:25.22,star,,0,0,0,,You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:26.77,star,,0,0,0,,Stop messin' around!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.80,0:04:29.11,star,,0,0,0,,What the hell's wrong with\N talking about Nagashima?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.11,0:04:30.40,star,,0,0,0,,That's right! That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:33.97,star,,0,0,0,,Don't butt in on other people's conversations\N  just because {\i1}you{\i0} hate baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.97,0:04:35.28,star,,0,0,0,,It's freedom of speech!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.74,0:04:37.71,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima's gonna win!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:40.57,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima's gonna win!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.14,0:04:44.00,star,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to shut up about him!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.62,0:04:45.74,star,,0,0,0,,Bastard...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.65,0:04:54.68,star,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.18,0:05:06.88,star,,0,0,0,,How's that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.08,0:05:18.22,star,,0,0,0,,Why is it Nagashima...?  Why is \N he the greatest third baseman...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:20.44,star,,0,0,0,,Pops could've...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.89,0:05:21.64,star,,0,0,0,,He could've...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.20,0:05:24.11,star,,0,0,0,,What're you spacing out for, Hyuuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.54,0:05:27.37,star,,0,0,0,,There's only twenty-nine left! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.20,0:05:36.85,star,,0,0,0,,What was that throw? There was no power in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.25,0:05:41.88,star,,0,0,0,,A pitcher can't look away for even a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:44.68,star,,0,0,0,,They always throw the ball with everything they have!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.77,0:05:48.51,star,,0,0,0,,Are listening to me, Hyuuma!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.51,0:05:49.14,star,,0,0,0,,Pops...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.98,0:05:51.45,star,,0,0,0,,Why do you always train me so hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:54.17,star,,0,0,0,,Is baseball really worth all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:58.28,star,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be like you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:01.16,star,,0,0,0,,Well, well, now this is a surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.76,0:06:03.47,star,,0,0,0,,Playing catch at this time of night?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:05.82,star,,0,0,0,,Guess there's some real\N weird people out there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.41,0:06:07.39,star,,0,0,0,,Ain't that the truth?
Comment: 0,0:06:07.39,0:06:09.39,star,,0,0,0,,nagashima mite ni yo yakyuu senshu sodattete gapogapo mogyute kontan nanda kore
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:08.83,star,,0,0,0,,Is this one of them scams?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.86,0:06:12.30,star,,0,0,0,,Gonna raise your boy into some kinda \N Nagashima-like baseball star and rake in the dough?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.49,0:06:18.17,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima would get angry if he \Nwas forced to be with some poor family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.49,0:06:18.17,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:  He also mentions that Hyuuma and his dad live in a tenement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.76,0:06:22.49,star,,0,0,0,,- Dammit...! \N{\c&HFFFFFF&}- Hyuuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.83,0:06:45.79,star,,0,0,0,,Serves you right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.33,0:06:53.34,star,,0,0,0,,What're you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.11,0:06:54.67,star,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Comment: 0,0:06:54.67,0:06:56.67,star,,0,0,0,,anata wa akuma no soukyuu to iwareta masoukyuu
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:57.84,star,,0,0,0,,The devil's fastball, also called the masoukyuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:07:01.15,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}:   "Masoukyuu" is a shortened version of\N  "aku[ma] no [soukyuu]" (the devil's fastball)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.46,0:07:01.15,star,,0,0,0,,...I thought I told you {\i1}never {\i0}to use it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.21,0:07:03.60,star,,0,0,0,,B-But they treated us like we're poor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.04,0:07:05.39,star,,0,0,0,,That's no excuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:07.55,star,,0,0,0,,Get on your knees and apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:11.77,star,,0,0,0,,Swear that you will never do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.14,0:07:12.60,star,,0,0,0,,I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:13.72,star,,0,0,0,,What did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.72,0:07:14.51,star,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.52,0:07:18.36,star,,0,0,0,,I know that you're frustrated! You have to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.13,0:07:20.40,star,,0,0,0,,Don't you think I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.13,0:07:22.59,star,,0,0,0,,The greatest third baseman...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:24.74,star,,0,0,0,,Anytime you hear about Nagashima...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.48,0:07:27.26,star,,0,0,0,,...you always get bitter and drink because you–
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:31.16,star,,0,0,0,,Father, don't be violent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.36,0:07:34.08,star,,0,0,0,,I know what you did back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.58,0:07:36.84,star,,0,0,0,,You were supposed to be the greatest\N third baseman ten years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.96,0:07:38.14,star,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.15,0:07:39.66,star,,0,0,0,,Don't talk about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.66,0:07:41.66,star,,0,0,0,,No, I'll say it! You bet I'll say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:44.08,star,,0,0,0,,All those times you've told me \N not to use the masoukyuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:45.12,star,,0,0,0,,...you've been—!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.12,0:07:46.08,star,,0,0,0,,You've been—!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.94,0:07:47.81,star,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:49.20,star,,0,0,0,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.44,0:07:53.61,star,,0,0,0,,Father! Stop it! Stop it, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.65,0:07:57.33,star,,0,0,0,,It's selfish...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.89,0:08:00.01,star,,0,0,0,,It's selfish to force me to live out {\i1}your {\i0}dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.28,0:08:01.18,star,,0,0,0,,It's so selfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.18,0:08:01.82,star,,0,0,0,,How dare...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.82,0:08:03.05,star,,0,0,0,,How dare you say that to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:07.58,star,,0,0,0,,- Stop it! Father!\N{\c&HFFFFFF&}- Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.80,0:08:08.52,star,,0,0,0,,Hyuuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.56,0:08:10.06,star,,0,0,0,,Hyuuma, run and get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.45,0:08:11.42,star,,0,0,0,,Pops, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.73,0:08:12.98,star,,0,0,0,,You coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:22.21,star,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.67,0:08:25.04,star,,0,0,0,,...I hate the kind of baseball Dad makes me play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.22,0:08:29.00,star,,0,0,0,,I hate Kawakami and Nagashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.71,0:08:37.39,star,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&}Tomorrow: A Party to Celebrate Nagashima's \N Admission into the Giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.18,0:08:52.68,star,,0,0,0,,Now then, everyone watching from\N  home, thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.68,0:08:55.36,star,,0,0,0,,We will now conduct an interview \N with Third Baseman, Nagashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:08:57.79,star,,0,0,0,,How about it? Anything to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.00,0:08:58.56,star,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:00.93,star,,0,0,0,,The Giants have a rich history behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.93,0:09:04.43,star,,0,0,0,,As long as I'm allowed to join their ranks,\N  I will do everything in my power...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:05.60,star,,0,0,0,,...to live up to their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.20,0:09:10.05,star,,0,0,0,,And now, former second baseman\N  and team senior, Chiba...
Comment: 0,0:09:06.20,0:09:10.05,star,,0,0,0,,e dewa koko de kyojingun no iidai na senpai shiba moto niruishi kara ekko no sebando san ga yururaremasu / And now, former second baseman and accomplished team senior, Shiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:12.44,star,,0,0,0,,...will entrust him with the Giants' number three jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.76,0:09:21.02,star,,0,0,0,,Take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.47,0:09:22.08,star,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.07,0:09:32.59,star,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kawakami-san, between you as first baseman and Chiba as second...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.59,0:09:36.67,star,,0,0,0,,...both of Japan's greatest first and second \N basemen are from the Giants, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:37.47,star,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:41.96,star,,0,0,0,,And now with the introduction of Nagashima-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.96,0:09:43.96,star,,0,0,0,,...it's very possible that the nation's \N greatest third baseman...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.96,0:09:47.16,star,,0,0,0,,...will come from the Giants as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.18,0:09:48.72,star,,0,0,0,,No, there's no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.05,0:09:50.84,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima-kun, do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.24,0:09:55.47,star,,0,0,0,,The greatest third baseman, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.79,0:09:57.13,star,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for the war...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:01.84,star,,0,0,0,,...then one might have already existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:03.71,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi Ittetsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.02,0:10:06.96,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun, the third baseman who never was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.68,0:10:08.96,star,,0,0,0,,Where are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.00,0:10:10.39,star,,0,0,0,,...and what are you doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.57,0:10:14.57,star,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:21.82,star,,0,0,0,,The third baseman who never was, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:23.32,star,,0,0,0,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:27.77,star,,0,0,0,,Hey, old man, don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.69,0:10:28.20,star,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.20,0:10:30.47,star,,0,0,0,,He actually talked back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:31.93,star,,0,0,0,,Still, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.93,0:10:33.36,star,,0,0,0,,It's already set, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.37,0:10:34.28,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima's gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.28,0:10:37.11,star,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm saying. That much is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.75,0:10:39.75,star,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.10,0:10:52.25,star,,0,0,0,,But you know? No matter what they say, \N I'lll be sure that damn kid makes it big.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.72,0:10:53.19,star,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.23,0:10:56.24,star,,0,0,0,,I'll make him into a real pitcher!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.07,0:11:02.24,star,,0,0,0,,Kawakami-san, don't just stand there \Nand smoke, help us out a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:03.06,star,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.52,0:11:05.52,star,,0,0,0,,Would you let us take a few pictures...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.52,0:11:09.01,star,,0,0,0,,...of you shaking hands with Nagashima\N  in front of the Giants' flag?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.27,0:11:10.77,star,,0,0,0,,Please do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.69,0:11:12.77,star,,0,0,0,,I see. Alright, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.56,0:11:16.85,star,,0,0,0,,Come over, Nagashima-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.68,0:11:18.24,star,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.12,0:11:31.04,star,,0,0,0,,It's the masoukyuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.58,0:11:32.08,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.72,0:11:34.40,star,,0,0,0,,Could Hoshi Ittetsu really be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.80,0:11:35.44,star,,0,0,0,,Masoukyuu?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.64,0:11:36.14,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.44,0:11:37.55,star,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.55,0:11:39.26,star,,0,0,0,,You see, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.38,0:11:43.78,star,,0,0,0,,Damn kid, stop moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:45.84,star,,0,0,0,,A kid like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.87,0:11:46.44,star,,0,0,0,,Kawakami-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:48.16,star,,0,0,0,,This is unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.81,0:11:49.71,star,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:56.76,star,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:06.29,star,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.55,0:12:07.86,star,,0,0,0,,Why would you do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.41,0:12:09.70,star,,0,0,0,,If you're silent, we can't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.16,0:12:13.16,star,,0,0,0,,Anyhow, if this kid really was \Nthe one who threw that ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.16,0:12:15.16,star,,0,0,0,,...then he's a bonafide genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.55,0:12:17.64,star,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what you just did?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.99,0:12:19.75,star,,0,0,0,,If you injured Nagashima...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.75,0:12:21.75,star,,0,0,0,,...then you'll be sent off to juvie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.31,0:12:23.04,star,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:26.50,star,,0,0,0,,Are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:29.60,star,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that your name's Hoshi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.52,0:12:32.60,star,,0,0,0,,Hell no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.15,0:12:34.60,star,,0,0,0,,Show me your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.07,0:12:38.20,star,,0,0,0,,These calluses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.33,0:12:40.92,star,,0,0,0,,It's almost like he's been playing \N baseball for twenty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.16,0:12:43.27,star,,0,0,0,,What about Nagashima!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.27,0:12:44.49,star,,0,0,0,,What about Kawakami!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.51,0:12:45.68,star,,0,0,0,,What about baseball!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.36,0:12:48.23,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:58.57,star,,0,0,0,,D-Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.58,0:13:03.71,star,,0,0,0,,It's terrifying that he can throw\N the masoukyuu at his age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:05.93,star,,0,0,0,,Nagashima-kun, I'll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.42,0:13:08.01,star,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:09.93,star,,0,0,0,,I need to know more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.93,0:13:11.07,star,,0,0,0,,I'm following after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.82,0:13:17.08,star,,0,0,0,,Dammit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.08,0:13:18.06,star,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.56,0:13:31.63,star,,0,0,0,,The Giants' third baseman who never was, Hoshi Ittetsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.09,0:13:33.95,star,,0,0,0,,What kind of life are you living now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.17,0:13:36.65,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:39.02,star,,0,0,0,,...you always were a man of bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.58,0:13:46.49,star,,0,0,0,,You joined the Giants in 1942 during \N  the height of the Pacific War.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:52.36,star,,0,0,0,,You were a prodigy of a player.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.14,0:13:55.74,star,,0,0,0,,I believed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.30,0:13:59.00,star,,0,0,0,,...that you were going to define the future of the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.40,0:14:01.85,star,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.02,0:14:05.58,star,,0,0,0,,...right before the team's first official match...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.62,0:14:09.12,star,,0,0,0,,...you were drafted into army and brought into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:23.48,star,,0,0,0,,In the midst of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.74,0:14:24.88,star,,0,0,0,,...you injured your shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:28.82,star,,0,0,0,,You injured something worth more than your life, and then you returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.96,0:14:27.93,star,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:34.11,star,,0,0,0,,1948.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.36,0:14:36.11,star,,0,0,0,,You rejoined the Giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.82,0:14:41.53,star,,0,0,0,,Normally, a person who's injured their shoulder...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.53,0:14:43.53,star,,0,0,0,,...loses their ability to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.22,0:14:45.53,star,,0,0,0,,But what a guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.85,0:14:49.74,star,,0,0,0,,You were a genius from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.65,0:14:51.43,star,,0,0,0,,Thinking back on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.48,0:14:54.08,star,,0,0,0,,It was a match...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.27,0:14:55.60,star,,0,0,0,,...near the beginning of that year's season.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:57.58,sign match2,,0,0,0,,{\org(372.163,238)\fscx110\fscy130\pos(406.269,304)\frz336.6\frx12\fry34}GIANTS: RED AND WHITE MATCH
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.30,0:14:59.60,star,,0,0,0,,You guarded third...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.82,0:15:00.96,star,,0,0,0,,...and I guarded first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.26,0:15:03.98,star,,0,0,0,,Play ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:11.72,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi's shoulder...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.73,0:15:12.50,star,,0,0,0,,He won't make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:17.02,star,,0,0,0,,Is it an out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.47,0:15:24.49,star,,0,0,0,,Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.88,0:15:31.18,star,,0,0,0,,To make the ball he threw from first look \Nlike it was about to hit the runner...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:33.09,star,,0,0,0,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:34.73,star,,0,0,0,,Was it pure luck, or...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:45.28,star,,0,0,0,,O-Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.38,0:15:47.56,star,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:49.56,star,,0,0,0,,It must be a throw Hoshi came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.98,0:15:51.12,star,,0,0,0,,What a genius idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:53.05,star,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:04.24,star,,0,0,0,,Just as expected, Kawakami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.82,0:16:05.88,star,,0,0,0,,You saw right through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.84,0:16:09.66,star,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I might've been the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.30,0:16:14.34,star,,0,0,0,,It's a technique I came up with to\Ncompensate for my shoulder.
Comment: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:17.04,star,,0,0,0,,shikashi tsuyo suru (to pass off) no wa itoki dake daze
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:17.04,star,,0,0,0,,But it'll only work once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.84,0:16:21.46,star,,0,0,0,,Exactly. The ball won't hit the runner, \Neven if it looks like it will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.70,0:16:26.57,star,,0,0,0,,If the runner figures that out, they'll \Nmake it to the base no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.14,0:16:28.46,star,,0,0,0,,Is that what you wanted to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:33.05,star,,0,0,0,,But that's not how it'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:36.02,star,,0,0,0,,If I were to hit them sometimes, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:37.16,star,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:39.76,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun, there's no doubt you're a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.16,0:16:42.54,star,,0,0,0,,The masoukyuu is a miracle you made happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.84,0:16:43.26,star,,0,0,0,,However..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.09,0:16:45.38,star,,0,0,0,,Let me give you some advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.24,0:16:46.72,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.21,0:16:48.48,star,,0,0,0,,...leave the Giants!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.66,0:16:50.48,star,,0,0,0,,What did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.25,0:16:52.80,star,,0,0,0,,Those who disgrace the team's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:54.45,star,,0,0,0,,...no matter how talented they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.76,0:16:56.45,star,,0,0,0,,...cannot remain on the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.06,0:16:57.85,star,,0,0,0,,Kawakami...!
Comment: 0,0:16:58.41,0:17:04.00,star,,0,0,0,,masokyuu no iryoku ga yagatte yattekuru muteki na kyojin gun ougon jidai no tame ni douryoku de yaku ni tatsu ka //
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.41,0:16:59.70,star,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:01.62,star,,0,0,0,,....how useful the masoukyuu will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.74,0:17:04.34,star,,0,0,0,,...when the Giants enter their golden age!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.73,0:17:05.34,star,,0,0,0,,Are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.34,0:17:06.64,star,,0,0,0,,Are you too much of an idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.64,0:17:07.65,star,,0,0,0,,to understand that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:09.98,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.48,0:17:12.73,star,,0,0,0,,Sawamura Eiji, in the days before he died in the war...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.48,0:17:20.97,t/n,,0,0,0,,{\u1}T/N Note{\u0}: Sawamura Eiji was a Giants pitcher who died in WWII. The Sawamura Award is given to Japanese pitchers in his honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.70,0:17:13.74,star,,0,0,0,,...left these words behind:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.66,0:17:17.20,star,,0,0,0,,"The pride I feel standing on the mound as a member of the Giants...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.22,0:17:20.97,star,,0,0,0,,...has never once allowed me to throw a beanball."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.82,0:17:30.55,star,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.62,0:17:33.14,star,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.23,0:17:35.23,star,,0,0,0,,The masoukyuu is just a beanball by a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:38.80,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.39,0:17:41.34,star,,0,0,0,,If things had been different, then there's no doubt...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.36,0:17:44.80,star,,0,0,0,,...you would have become the greatest third baseman in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.52,0:17:47.32,star,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.68,0:17:49.47,star,,0,0,0,,This is goodbye...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.85,0:17:50.43,star,,0,0,0,,...Kawakami-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.89,0:17:52.35,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.84,0:18:01.54,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.62,0:18:09.25,star,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:11.00,star,,0,0,0,,Stop that! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.32,0:18:19.27,star,,0,0,0,,Excuse us for causing so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:20.49,star,,0,0,0,,We're truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:22.48,star,,0,0,0,,- It's really no problem. \N {\c&HFFFFFF&}- Yeah, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.36,0:18:26.52,star,,0,0,0,,Nee-chan, I can't count on you for anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.97,0:18:29.28,star,,0,0,0,,Why'd you let Pops drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.28,0:18:30.06,star,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:31.08,star,,0,0,0,,I'm done with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.08,0:18:34.03,star,,0,0,0,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.45,0:18:35.45,star,,0,0,0,,Take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.75,0:18:37.27,star,,0,0,0,,All of this is your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.27,0:18:39.27,star,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.22,0:18:42.96,star,,0,0,0,,He really outdid himself this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.14,0:18:46.68,star,,0,0,0,,But how is any of this my fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.25,0:18:48.25,star,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.69,0:18:50.09,star,,0,0,0,,You threw the masoukyuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:52.09,star,,0,0,0,,...at Nagashima-sam when he doesn't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.41,0:18:54.33,star,,0,0,0,,Why {\i1}wouldn't{\i0} Dad get mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.00,0:18:56.28,star,,0,0,0,,- Y-You guys saw that? \N {\c&HFFFFFF&}- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.55,0:18:58.73,star,,0,0,0,,The broadcast switched away before it was shown...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.73,0:19:00.72,star,,0,0,0,,...so we couldn't see who threw the ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.88,0:19:02.99,star,,0,0,0,,...but Dad knew the moment he saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.48,0:19:05.30,star,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.47,0:19:06.95,star,,0,0,0,,He didn't have to do all this, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.95,0:19:08.35,star,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.38,0:19:11.31,star,,0,0,0,,I've fallen, but I'm still Hoshi Ittetsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.35,0:19:14.23,star,,0,0,0,,You know what would happen if they traced that bullshit back to my son?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.67,0:19:17.73,star,,0,0,0,,...I'd be embarrassed to see my old Giants teammates!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:19.86,star,,0,0,0,,- What was that about the Giants? \N{\c&HFFFFFF&} - What? The Giants?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:23.72,star,,0,0,0,,Sorry for bothering you, or somethin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:25.93,star,,0,0,0,,It's all calmed down now, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:27.93,star,,0,0,0,,...please feel free to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.12,0:19:30.92,star,,0,0,0,,You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:32.21,star,,0,0,0,,Pops, you liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.38,0:19:34.53,star,,0,0,0,,The reason you did all this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.53,0:19:36.53,star,,0,0,0,,...isn't because I threw the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.29,0:19:38.48,star,,0,0,0,,It's not because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.71,0:19:40.48,star,,0,0,0,,It's because it's the ball you came up with...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.48,0:19:42.48,star,,0,0,0,,...and Nagashima saw through it, just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.27,0:19:45.09,star,,0,0,0,,Pops, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.40,0:19:46.88,star,,0,0,0,,The third baseman who never was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:48.41,star,,0,0,0,,...lost to Nagashima!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.57,0:19:51.92,star,,0,0,0,,You lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.85,0:20:05.65,star,,0,0,0,,Look, it's just like I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.92,0:20:07.14,star,,0,0,0,,You say that, but Hyuuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.67,0:20:09.14,star,,0,0,0,,You're frustrated too, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:10.90,star,,0,0,0,,You're sad, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:12.20,star,,0,0,0,,Shut up, stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.38,0:20:13.93,star,,0,0,0,,It's too late to wipe away your tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.42,0:20:16.30,star,,0,0,0,,It's written all over your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.35,0:20:19.13,star,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.19,0:20:20.37,star,,0,0,0,,Nee-chan, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.37,0:20:21.04,star,,0,0,0,,Moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:22.00,star,,0,0,0,,Ugly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.01,0:20:23.60,star,,0,0,0,,No one's ever gonna marry you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:24.75,star,,0,0,0,,It's just so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.21,0:20:26.43,star,,0,0,0,,Dad, you always thought that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.85,0:20:27.61,star,,0,0,0,,...as long as you had the masoukyuu...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.78,0:20:29.78,star,,0,0,0,,...you could make yourself believe that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.88,0:20:31.61,star,,0,0,0,,...you were the greatest third baseman, didn't you?
Comment: 0,0:20:31.61,0:20:33.61,star,,0,0,0,,kawaisou. masokyuu daiikkai otousan koso shijou saidai no meisanruishi datte shinjitte  itakatta wz nd
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.66,0:20:35.53,star,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:37.93,star,,0,0,0,,Still, what a horrible way to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:43.23,star,,0,0,0,,...Hoshi-kun wouldn't want to see his old teammates right now, would he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.36,0:20:44.48,star,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll go back for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.38,0:20:48.63,star,,0,0,0,,This house is cursed by baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.38,0:20:52.28,star,,0,0,0,,Every day since I was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:54.55,star,,0,0,0,,...let alone play...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.89,0:20:56.72,star,,0,0,0,,...all I've ever been allowed to do is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.42,0:21:05.47,star,,0,0,0,,I-It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.77,0:21:07.22,star,,0,0,0,,A ball from that hole...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.47,0:21:08.34,star,,0,0,0,,Is it a fluke?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.02,0:21:14.34,star,,0,0,0,,Dammit! I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:15.97,star,,0,0,0,,...to play cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.46,0:21:17.97,star,,0,0,0,,...and spin tops too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.61,0:21:20.61,star,,0,0,0,,But even if I wanted to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.92,0:21:23.59,star,,0,0,0,,...you'd only let me do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:26.40,star,,0,0,0,,For five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.10,0:21:27.77,star,,0,0,0,,Six!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.75,0:21:29.55,star,,0,0,0,,Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.22,0:21:33.90,star,,0,0,0,,Training.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:37.94,star,,0,0,0,,It was horrifying training that allowed\N this miracle to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.11,0:21:43.70,star,,0,0,0,,If his speed and control were off by just a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.70,0:21:45.82,star,,0,0,0,,...then the ball would go in a \Ncompletely different direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.27,0:21:48.29,star,,0,0,0,,I can't back down now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.27,0:21:53.26,star,,0,0,0,,Batting is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.35,0:21:56.95,star,,0,0,0,,If the ball isn't hit in just the right way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.14,0:21:58.84,star,,0,0,0,,...then it'll fly in the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.08,0:22:02.12,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi Ittetsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.60,0:22:06.20,star,,0,0,0,,To see if you're qualified to raise a genius like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.78,0:22:07.96,star,,0,0,0,,I, former pro...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.33,0:22:10.59,star,,0,0,0,,...Line Driver Kawakami, will test you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.47,0:22:13.21,star,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.97,0:22:15.69,star,,0,0,0,,Pops!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.56,0:22:19.59,star,,0,0,0,,Oops, I forget this wasn't a stadium.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.59,0:22:20.51,star,,0,0,0,,Amazing...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.91,0:22:22.06,star,,0,0,0,,How amazing was that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.35,0:22:23.50,star,,0,0,0,,It was like a magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:24.84,star,,0,0,0,,Just as expected!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.15,0:22:27.60,star,,0,0,0,,You caught it and got into a throwing pose without even thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.10,0:22:29.10,star,,0,0,0,,I'm glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.04,0:22:32.64,star,,0,0,0,,Hoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.19,0:22:34.37,star,,0,0,0,,...this time for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.59,0:22:37.31,star,,0,0,0,,...I'm counting on you to raise the greatest pitcher out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.65,0:22:40.37,star,,0,0,0,,For the Giants of tomorrow, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.78,0:22:42.03,star,,0,0,0,,Hyuuma, you screwed up, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.64,0:22:44.84,star,,0,0,0,,To think that you'd send a ball back in that direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.02,0:22:46.35,star,,0,0,0,,Y-You're wrong, Pops!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.84,0:22:48.79,star,,0,0,0,,Someone hit it back from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.02,0:22:51.82,star,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.11,0:22:55.23,star,,0,0,0,,The only batter in Japan who could do something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.44,0:22:56.96,star,,0,0,0,,...is Kawakami Tetsuharu.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.29,0:23:00.01,star,,0,0,0,,Kawakami...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.50,0:23:06.27,star,,0,0,0,,Just like we thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.40,0:23:07.55,star,,0,0,0,,That man from behind, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.82,0:23:20.84,star,,0,0,0,, Look, Hyuuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.18,0:23:23.87,star,,0,0,0,,That constellation represents every position, each member of the Giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.68,0:23:28.60,star,,0,0,0,,Once in the past, I was one of those shining stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:32.78,star,,0,0,0,,But as I am now, it's out of my reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.36,0:23:34.01,star,,0,0,0,,Hyuuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.71,0:23:36.38,star,,0,0,0,,Climb until you reach it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.07,0:23:39.05,star,,0,0,0,,Make yourself the brightest star...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.27,0:23:41.62,star,,0,0,0,,...right in the dead center!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.32,0:23:43.02,star,,0,0,0,,Hyuuma, my boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.41,0:23:45.51,star,,0,0,0,,Aim for the star of glory!
